 ## 1. Executive Directive
 
 IOI's next task is not another architecture expansion or a broad application
 queue. It is to turn the architecture already in canon into one undeniable
 product proof, then expand only through evidence-bearing distributed,
 federated, embodied, and public-economic profiles.
 
 The target remains:
 
 > IOI is the open operating stack for bounded distributed autonomous systems.
 > L0 makes one autonomous institution governable and distributable across its
 > admitted compute, state, verification, human, and embodied nodes. AIIP makes
 > selective positive-surplus cooperation between separately sovereign
 > institutions contractible. IOI L1 supplies optional shared trust and
 > economic finality only where measured demand justifies it.
 
 The first terminal product proof is narrower:
 
 > An OutcomeRoom-backed bounded software-change institution that a new operator
 > can create, govern, run, inspect, improve, recover, export, and retire through
 > supported product surfaces; it admits first-party and local agents, preserves
 > one durable GoalRun across replaceable sessions and model routes, independently
 > verifies a proposed change, obtains exact-effect authority, executes once or
 > refuses, and exports a replayable evidence chain.
 
 This is the minimum profile that can prove the stack is coherent without
 requiring multi-node continuity, cross-system federation, public settlement,
 or physical actuation. It is the selected first profile, not the definition of
 a bounded DAS and not a reason to narrow later horizons.
 
 The expansion order is fixed:
 
 ```text
 program and claim control
   -> bounded-System constitutional core
   -> deployment, membership, transition, and fencing truth
   -> generic pursuit and result seam
   -> OutcomeRoom flagship DAS
   -> admitted participants, local agents, and shared frontier
   -> honest product workspaces and application catalog
   -> local ontology and action semantics
   -> enterprise learning and bounded improvement
   -> single-node undeniable product proof
   -> two-failure-domain continuity
   -> useful same-system distributed work and embodied pre-live proof
   -> AIIP federation contracts
   -> two-sovereign Internet-of-Intelligence proof
   -> demand-gated connected/secured services and optional L1
 ```
 
 No older phase list may reorder this spine.
 
