 compatibility_and_migration
 evidence_index
 remaining_nonclaims
 rollback_or_stop_rule
 source_provenance
 ```
 
 This is internal planning syntax, not a new canonical envelope.
 
 ### 4.2 Admission rule
 
 A work item starts only when:
 
 - its claim can fail;
-- its owner documents and current status rows have been read;
+- its owner documents and current work-item records have been read;
 - its selected deployment profile and nonclaims are explicit;
 - upstream contracts are verified or explicitly simulated;
 - metrics and thresholds are frozen before observation;
 - every consequential effect names its final invoker;
 - applicable `PG-*` gates are mapped without changing their definitions;
 - negative and inconclusive results have a durable retention path;
 - the product projection, if any, cannot fabricate missing owner truth.
 
 ### 4.3 Completion bundle
 
 No schema, route, UI, test, or receipt closes a work item alone. A verified item
 contains all applicable parts of:
 
 ```text
 owner-approved contract and invariants
   + registered schema and generated Rust/TypeScript form
   + compatibility and migration rules
   + Rust daemon admission/execution path
   + Agentgres operation/head/root/receipt/replay path
   + authority, safety, IFC, budget, fence, and idempotency checks
   + positive, negative, substitution, stale-state, and fault evidence
   + policy-filtered product projection and honest degraded states
-  + status-index updates
+  + work-item-record update and regenerated local program-state projection
   + exported evidence index
   + explicit remaining nonclaims
 ```
 
 An item is blocked, not partial-success, when a required owner boundary is
 replaced by a fixture or manual edit.
 
 ### 4.4 Stage state
 
 Stages use:
 
 | State | Meaning |
 | --- | --- |
 | `pending` | Prerequisites or activation decision not yet satisfied. |
 | `active` | At least one admitted work item is executing. |
 | `evidence_ready` | Positive path exists; adversarial and release evidence is under review. |
 | `verified` | The stage exit proof and required rails close. |
 | `blocked` | A named external decision, authority, dependency, or environment prevents progress. |
 | `superseded` | Canon changed the stage; evidence is retained and the master is revised. |
 
 Only proof changes a stage to `verified`.
 
