 ## 12. Adversarial Proof Matrix
 
 Every active stage selects applicable rows:
 
 | Failure class | Minimum question |
 | --- | --- |
 | Identity substitution | Can a different principal, session, origin, factor, or device replay the action? |
 | Body/ref substitution | Can the signed or admitted hash be reused with changed content, target, destination, or version? |
 | Stale state | Does a stale head, epoch, root, grant, lease, profile, or policy reach an effect? |
 | Authority bypass | Can UI, client, harness, connector, MCP, provider, or copied receipt fields mint power? |
 | Route exposure / authorization fork | Is every externally reachable route classified, and can an MCP-only, adapter-only, or unregistered path reach a different policy or final-invoker path? |
 | Coverage overclaim | Can discovery, observation, attribution, mediation, or receipt presence be misreported as prevention, especially after adapter loss, offline transition, version drift, or an opaque-runtime bypass? |
 | Information-flow attack | Can untrusted instructions or derived data cross to a forbidden tool, model, tenant, or destination? |
 | Retry/ambiguity | Can timeout, restart, or uncertain external completion duplicate an effect? |
 | Writer/failover fault | Can an old, foreign, partitioned, or deposed writer act? |
 | Truth/projection split | Can cache, UI, search, count, or compatibility data become accepted truth? |
 | Evidence producer conflict | Does proof require trusting the same producer whose behavior is being proved? |
 | Verifier manipulation | Can the candidate select, alter, expose, or overfit the judgment path? |
 | Budget reset | Can branch, retry, order, account, or provider fallback evade finite limits? |
 | Cross-tenant leak | Can counts, recents, caches, routes, artifacts, memory, or exports reveal another scope? |
 | Membership/claim leak | Does pairing, discovery, rank, or contribution grant membership, credit allocation, payout, or authority? |
 | Semantic escalation | Can mapping, compatibility, assertion, or ontology membership authorize an action? |
 | Dependency outage | Are unavailable, denied, degraded, recovery, and partial-dependency states honest and safe? |
 | Supply substitution | Does provider/model/worker/tool fallback change rights or semantics without review/evidence? |
 | Release/update substitution | Can unsigned, revoked, downgraded, digest-mismatched, or manifest-substituted install/update material execute or replace the admitted build? |
 | Restore-byte or secret substitution | Can same-size changed bytes, loose plaintext, foreign ciphertext, a stale preflight, or an incomplete manifest mutate the target before full verification and destination-local re-resolution? |
 | Activation/cleanup loss | Can a failed, unknown, late, partial, or superseded change steal the active head, or can deleting a parent erase an unresolved resource-cleanup duty? |
 | Physical safety fault | Can remote/model/chain failure disable local veto, heartbeat, deterministic motion, or e-stop? |
 | Economic theater | Does cooperation/network value disappear after subsidy, risk, or token appreciation is removed? |
 
 Positive tests demonstrate a path. These failures determine whether the claim
 is bounded.
 
